#: JSP_HELPPAGE_DEFAULT_CONTENT
msgid "\\u003ch1\\u003eHTMLEditorPortlet\\u003c/h1\\u003e \\u003cp\\u003e&nbsp; \\u003cp\\u003eUse this portlet to create/edit/view a HTML page or plain text page.\\u003c/p\\u003e \\u003cp\\u003e&nbsp;\\u003c/p\\u003e \\u003cp\\u003eTo edit/create a page, click \\'Edit\\' button on the frame of the window, then:\\u003c/p\\u003e \\u003cul\\u003e \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eSpecify the height and width of the desired size of the portlet window.They can be the number of pixels(e.g., use 440 instead of 440px) or percentage(e.g.,100%).If not specified, the default value would be the one you last saved. If never specified before, the value specified in the preferences of the HTMLEditorPortlet.xml will be used.If the input format is incorrect,an alert box will pop up.\\u003c/p\\u003e \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eTo add a new Custom Control item,enter the Custom Key(the item shows up in the \\'Custom Dropdown Text\\') and Custom Value (the value associated with the item shows up in the text area)and click \\'Add\\' button,then the newly added item will show up in the \\'Custom Dropdown Text\\' menu.If the custom key already exists, the new corresponding value will overwrite the old one.If want to add scopedpath to \\'Custom Dropdown Text\\', use $[bluh] as opposed to ScopedPath syntax ${bluh}\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eTo delete a Custom Control item,enter the desired Custom Key and click \\'Delete\\' button, the item will be removed from the \\'Custom Dropdown Text\\' menu.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eUse the text area and the tools(including \\'Custom Dropdown Text\\' menu) available in the palette to create/edit a page.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eChecking \\'View Source\\' box will display the HTML source code.Edition can be made here directly as well.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eUnchecking \\'View Source\\' box will get page back to View mode. \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eClick the \\'Save\\' button to save the changes made and it will go back to the View mode. If nothing is changed, nothing will be saved and it will return to the View mode.\\u003c/p\\u003e \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eClick the \\'Cancel\\' button will simply return to the View mode.\\u003c/p\\u003e \\u003c/ul\\u003e \\u003cp\\u003e&nbsp;\\u003c/p\\u003e \\u003cp\\u003eNote: Above edition can also be done through the portal\\'s Personalize-\\u003ePreferences or DAC.\\u003c/p\\u003e"
msgstr ""

